I remember a story that someone sent us
a long time ago.

830
01:02:51,350 --> 01:02:53,728
He returned home from a business trip.

831
01:02:53,811 --> 01:02:56,773
His wife was nowhere to be seen
and had left him a letter.

832
01:02:56,856 --> 01:02:58,733
She had another man.

833
01:02:58,816 --> 01:03:00,693
He must've been heartbroken.

834
01:03:00,777 --> 01:03:03,780
Username 2431 says,
"He must've been flustered.

835
01:03:03,863 --> 01:03:07,325
That's like breaking up
through a text message.

836
01:03:07,408 --> 01:03:09,118
Breakups need to be respectful too.

837
01:03:09,702 --> 01:03:14,123
I think his wife was
disrespectful and inconsiderate."

838
01:03:14,707 --> 01:03:18,586
Username 3544 says,
"Your wife was a terrible woman."

839
01:03:19,504 --> 01:03:23,049
Username 9217 says,
"She probably had her reasons."

840
01:03:23,132 --> 01:03:24,342
Username 7756 says,

841
01:03:24,425 --> 01:03:27,053
"That's right. We should hear
both sides of the story."

842
01:03:28,888 --> 01:03:30,348
That's true.

843
01:03:30,431 --> 01:03:33,100
It's important to listen to both sides.

844
01:03:33,184 --> 01:03:34,769
But this is what I think.

845
01:03:34,852 --> 01:03:37,021
Their faults aside,

846
01:03:37,104 --> 01:03:40,817
I believe breakups should be
respectful and considerate.

847
01:03:53,496 --> 01:03:54,413
What's up there?

848
01:03:56,332 --> 01:03:58,084
Do you think

849
01:03:58,960 --> 01:04:01,003
my grandpa is really in heaven?

850
01:04:01,087 --> 01:04:03,923
I'm not sure.
I have a hard time believing that.

851
01:04:04,006 --> 01:04:04,841
It's outer space.

852
01:04:06,384 --> 01:04:07,635
Thanks for the text.

853
01:04:10,888 --> 01:04:12,723
Do you fart?

854
01:04:12,807 --> 01:04:13,683
